ingredientsDesc: A.	Anti-Inhibin A-Coated Microtitration Strips:coated with anti-Inhibin βA subunit antibody immobilized to the inside wall of each well.B.	Inhibin A Standard A/Sample Diluent:containing 0 pg/mL dimeric Inhibin A in fetal bovine serum with a non-mercury preservative.C.	Inhibin A Standards:labeled B-G, containing concentrations of approximately 10, 30, 100, 250, 500, and 1000 pg/mL dimeric Inhibin A in fetal bovine serum with a non-mercury preservative.D.	Inhibin A Controls:Levels I and II, containing low and high concentrations of Dimeric Inhibin A infetal bovine serum with a non-mercury preservative.E.	Inhibin A Sample Buffer A:containing a protein-based buffer with a non-mercury preservative.F.	Inhibin A Sample Buffer B:   containing a protein-based buffer with a non-mercury preservative.G.	Inhibin A Antibody-Enzyme Conjugate Concentrate:containing 0.6 mL of a solution of anti-Inhibin α-subunit antibody conjugate to horseradish peroxidase in a protein-based buffer with a non-mercury presercative

H.	TMB Chromogen Solution:containing a solution of tetramethylbenzidine (TMB) in citrate buffer with hydrogen peroxide.I.	Stopping Solution:containing 0.2 M sulfuric acid.J.	Inhibin A Conjugate Diluent:containing a protein-based buffer with a non-mercury preservative.K.	Wash Concentrate:containing 60 mL buffered saline with a nonionic detergent.
